[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":169},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F02\u002F06\u002Fhow-to-clear-terminal-screen\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F02\u002F06\u002Fhow-to-clear-terminal-screen\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F02\u002F06\u002Fhow-to-clear-terminal-screen\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F02\u002F06\u002Fhow-to-clear-terminal-screen\u002F":144,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F02\u002F06\u002Fhow-to-clear-terminal-screen\u002F":153},"\u002Fother\u002F20220206\u002F4243268872\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":125,"date":126,"description":127,"extension":128,"lang":129,"meta":130,"navigation":131,"path":132,"readingMinutes":133,"seo":134,"standalone":135,"stem":136,"tags":137,"tldr":140,"updated":141,"url":142,"__hash__":143},"content\u002Fen\u002FMisc\u002Fhow-to-clear-terminal-screen.md","How to Clear the Terminal Screen (Mac and Windows)","2486388247",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":119},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,34,40,43,72,78,91,94,113],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Whether you're on Mac or Windows, you probably use a terminal (or Command Prompt) constantly during dev — and it piles up output fast. Quick note on how to clear the screen.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"clearing-the-terminal","Clearing the terminal",[17,25,26],{},"Your terminal might look like this — lots of output:",[17,28,29],{},[30,31],"img",{"alt":32,"src":33},"Mac","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-02-06%2021.05.38.png",[17,35,36],{},[30,37],{"alt":38,"src":39},"Windows","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F2022-02-06_21-11-46.png",[17,41,42],{},"It doesn't break anything, but it gets visually annoying. Type one of these to clear:",[44,45,46,58],"ul",{},[47,48,49,50],"li",{},"Mac\n",[44,51,52],{},[47,53,54],{},[55,56,57],"code",{},"clear",[47,59,60,61],{},"Windows\n",[44,62,63,67],{},[47,64,65],{},[55,66,57],{},[47,68,69],{},[55,70,71],{},"cls",[17,73,74],{},[30,75],{"alt":76,"src":77},"Mac after clear","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F2022-02-06%2021.07.30.png",[79,80,81],"blockquote",{},[17,82,83,87,88,90],{},[84,85,86],"strong",{},"Note","\nThe ",[55,89,57],{}," command doesn't actually wipe the terminal's contents — it just scrolls the cursor down so the visible screen looks empty. Scroll up and you'll still see the old output.",[17,92,93],{},"There's also a keyboard shortcut version that's a bit faster:",[44,95,96,106],{},[47,97,49,98],{},[44,99,100,103],{},[47,101,102],{},"Command + K",[47,104,105],{},"Control + L",[47,107,60,108],{},[44,109,110],{},[47,111,112],{},"Ctrl + L (older versions seem to have been Ctrl + K)",[17,114,115,116,118],{},"On Mac specifically, Command + K is the \"real\" clear — it wipes scrollback too. Control + L behaves like ",[55,117,57],{},".",{"title":120,"searchDepth":121,"depth":121,"links":122},"",2,[123,124],{"id":14,"depth":121,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":121,"text":23},"Misc","2022-02-06 20:52:22","Whether you're on Mac or Windows, the terminal piles up output fast and it gets noisy. Quick note on the commands and keyboard shortcuts that clear the screen — including the distinction between \"actually wiping scrollback\" vs. \"just scrolling the cursor down so the screen looks empty\".","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002Fhow-to-clear-terminal-screen","1",{"title":6,"description":127},false,"en\u002FMisc\u002Fhow-to-clear-terminal-screen",[138,139,38,32],"Terminal","Command Prompt",null,"2023-07-30 11:02:58","\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F02\u002F06\u002Fhow-to-clear-terminal-screen\u002F","wJrNyxZXfHFMAuy3nyW2I494PuTeuyp2eTca7Z37e0c",{"newer":145,"older":149},{"url":146,"title":147,"date":148},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F02\u002F07\u002Fdiscord-2fa-setup-guide\u002F","How to Enable 2FA on Discord (Step-by-Step Guide to Protect Your Account)","2022-02-07 10:20:01",{"url":150,"title":151,"date":152},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F02\u002F02\u002Fudemy-translate-subtitles-in-real-time-with-js\u002F","Udemy Tip: Translate Subtitles in Real Time With a Translation Extension + JS Snippet","2022-02-02 22:41:09",[154,159,164],{"url":155,"title":156,"date":157,"readingMinutes":158},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F06\u002F23\u002Fmac-stats-menu-bar-system-monitor\u002F","Stats — The Free Open-Source macOS Menu Bar System Monitor I Use Every Day (CPU, GPU, Temperature, Network)","2026-06-23 10:00:00","5",{"url":160,"title":161,"date":162,"readingMinutes":163},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F26\u002Fhow-much-does-a-blog-really-earn-with-google-adsense\u002F","Can a Blog Really Make Tens of Thousands of Dollars a Month? Real Google AdSense Numbers, Explained","2026-05-26 21:00:00","6",{"url":165,"title":166,"date":167,"readingMinutes":168},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F18\u002Fvscode-disable-integrated-browser-auto-open\u002F","VSCode Opens Every Link in the Integrated Browser? How to Disable Auto Takeover","2026-05-18 14:30:00","4",1784011705430]